text.__SUMMARY__: Artemidiconus selenae is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conorbidae.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans, therefore live ones should be handled carefully or not at all.
text.Description: The maximum recorded shell length is 19 mm.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off Northern Brazil.
text.Habitat: Minimum recorded depth is 18 m. Maximum recorded depth is 135 m.
